	"description": "The N+1 query problem is a performance issue you might face while building APIs,\nregardless of whether they&#x27;re GraphQL or REST APIs.\n\nIn fact, this problem occurs when your application needs to return a set of data\nthat includes related nested data – for example, a post that includes comments.\n\nBut how can you fix this problem? To avoid this issue, you should understand\nwhat is it and how it occurs.\n\nSo in this tutorial, you&#x27;ll learn what the N+1 query problem is, why it is easy\nto fall into it,",
